title: National Geographic Magazine Vol. 09 - 03. March 1898
description:
The National Geographic Magazine, an illustrated monthly, Vol IX, the March Number.
It includes the following articles:
  • Dwellings of the Saga-time in Iceland, Greenland, and Vineland, by Cornelia Horsford
  • Completion of the La Boca Dock
  • Two Hundred Miles up the Kuskokwim, by Charles Hallock
  • The Mt St Elias Expedition of Prince Luigi Amadeo of Savoy, by Eliza Ruhamah Scidmore
  • The Origin of the French Canadians
  • The Height of Mt Rainier, by Richard U. Goode
  • Geographic Work by the Bureau of American Ethnology, by W. J. McGee
  • A Relic of the Lewis and Clarke Expedition, by Cyrus C. Babb
  • An Interesting Rumor Concerning Andree, by John Hyde
  • Geographic Names in West Greenland, by Ralph S. Tarr
